This is an ongoing thing with her that I have ran out of steam for. So we went to Dunham Massey instead and looked at the old stuff. I found this bowl from 1790 that’s giving 2000s Live Laugh Love/a man with his dog on Hinge:

He once played a game with me (for too long) where he pretended to be racing the planets, but he was actually methodically ordering them - by what characteristics I don’t know - and I just had to be like OH MY GODDD every time the moon beat Saturn, as if it hadn’t been calculated

I’m not glad that your Mum is like that, but part of me is because my Dad is also like that. Not the badge wearing kind, but the “I don’t have a problem with it but (insert transphobic comment here)” kind. Very tiresome. I have also given up and normally just divert the convo if it comes up. The badge is a very bold move though, when did she start this?

I LOVE this bowl, or whatever the word for ironically loving something is. Is it next to a 250 year old wood carving that says “You don’t have to be crazy to till the fields, but it helps!”

message:
This is just the sort of update I was hoping for. I would ask further pasta questions but in text form it won’t be very funny.

Paris is lovely. I have been to the louvre but only quickly tbh, it’s so big I guess you could spend a week in there. ALSO Mona Lisa, you’re right. Bad vibes there. Weird. It is a lovely painting up close-ish though.

Then I went to Rodin’s garden, favourite thing I’ve seen so far. I’d heard of him but never checked his stuff out (I think maybe that book I read recently spoke about him). There was a lot of anguished statues in a lovely garden with very nice trees and plants. Right up my alley

Just in Mon Matre getting a beer then I’m going to find this graveyard that’s meant to be good for some reason. Unsure what I’m doing later but my new friend Alexi who lives above me said he’ll get in touch because he’s going out for drinks

Tell me the best thing you have seen all of today

message: This is funny. The amount of people who just reply ‘you’ to that is awful. I would like to say that the best thing I’ve seen today is the film I just saw but it was the new Ken Loach film so it was obviously very bleak. My colleague (weird word but I guess most appropriate here) was leaving work like ‘what are you doing tonight’ and I said I don’t know I might just watch a film and he said WELL I’m going to see this one about Syrian immigrants and community tensions do you want to come and I said OKAY and then had to watch a big dog eat a small dog and see a very sad man’s pub get destroyed so now I’m not sure whether that was the right response. This was a drawn out reply and I’m not even sure it answers your question

author: conall
message:
I did get quite close but it was only because there was a big tour group in front of me, they moved and I got right up to the little velvet rope. Maybe Sad Paris Zoë wasn’t as fortunate (not a great weekend for her overall by the sounds of it). I was going to take a very bad picture with my thumb covering the painting on the lens because I thought that would be funny, but I couldn’t commit. A low point for me really.

Definitely get your arse to Rodin’s garden if you’re ever here again, it’s beautiful.

No! The one in Mon Matre with lots of not famous people in it. If I get my boxes and bike sorted today I will be going to see Oscar Wilde’s grave which is in the same graveyard as Doors man. It’ll probably just be fine but I read Dorian Gray recently so I figure why not.

I have bad news about the notebook, I haven’t taken it anywhere because the rural french trained me to forget about it! No signatures in Paris. Very disappointing. I’ve lost my groove with it.

- This prawn sandwich is nice

- ⁠Uber driver was great this morning, he was trying to get me to convert to islam but drove very quickly
- ⁠Looking at every woman and thinking “lol bet you kiss your mates when you’re drunk, silly women”

message:
Hey, I’m gonna get an early night, I had a bath and it’s turned me to mush. I’m sure lots of thoughts are swimming around your brain atm, I’m well aware I don’t understand many of them. That doesn’t need to be fixed right away, or ever really. You’re your own person and we all have our own private slice of hell in our brains.

I’ll ease off contacting you and let you control the pace of our interactions for now, I say this so you don’t worry that I’m annoyed or hurt by you. There’s nothing you need to beat yourself up about, you just need some alone time, we all do at some point. Take whatever space you need.

Excuse this essay, I hope you’re having as good an evening as you can given the circumstances. Finally I hope your neck isn’t giving you too much grief. Speak to you whenever’s right x

author: conall
message:
I’ll also say: I’m actually running out of ways to describe how ace it has been meeting you. I still can’t quite believe it tbh. Idk why I feel some hesitation writing this but I know that’s very silly. I think I am also scared in my own way of giving myself over entirely to this, but I JUST can’t help it. Even things that are “issues” we chat about and just agree what each of us can do to help the other. It sounds really small but it means so much to me that we can communicate like that. ANYWAY, I remember reading somewhere that falling in love is a thing we can’t help, that’s why we call it falling. I didn’t really get it at the time but it’s starting to make sense now.

Weather report over

author: Zoë “cringe” Turner
message: I hope you know that I don’t take anything you told me last night lightly. I’ve intuited that it’s not something you’d want big sad or dramatic reactions to, so I guess I’m just choosing to concentrate on where you are now, which is what I think you want to do also. I just want to stress how blown away I am by you all the time, and I’ll keep trying to show it as much as I feel it (difficult because so much feel). That is all xxx

author: conall
message:
Thanks babes, as EVER you have intuited correctly. I feel much lighter having told you. I am mostly an open book but like everyone I have things that I just don’t let people in on. It means a lot that you’re the first person I’ve met since that I can talk to about it, that isn’t someone I’m paying. Others exist in my life to chat these things through with now, I know that, but I’m healed from it all now so it’s mostly just context for you to understand why I think the way I do about certain topics like connection, friends, relationships, blah blah.

To big myself up a little bit, I AM very proud of what I’ve managed to do in the last few years of my life. I’m not great at doing that but idk it’s good sometimes to recognise how far you’ve come. I’m very happy that we’ve met at this point in both of our lives. Words fail me to finish this sentence, but know that you mean a lot to me.

Frankly I need to stop talking about how much you mean to me for now because it’s getting me quite emotional and I can’t just wander round glassy eyed all day hahahahahahahaha

Love you loads x

author: Zoë “cringe” Turner
message: I guess to me you do seem a bit disconnected from yourself, and I think that’s only really been obvious since you went on holiday, but you might’ve been feeling like this before. I know that habits are super important to you and you’ve just been pulled in lots of different directions the last few weeks, maybe not putting yourself as very high priority, and feeling under appreciated for it. So maybe it’s about refocusing on yourself, looking at the next few weeks ahead (or just few days if that’s easier) and figuring out where your time is there/how you(YOU) want to spend it

author: Zoë “cringe” Turner
message: And as an aside to that, you shouldn’t be worried about saying no to me. I know that might not be an issue here but just to note that if you feel like you can’t say it to other people at the moment, remember that I am gonna understand if and when you’re just not feeling something we had planned or not able to commit to something I ask about. Obviously that’s to a degree / contextual but basically if you’re ever feeling a certain way I can just adjust my expectations to that and then that’s absolutely fine with me - don’t think you have to be holding this up all the time is maybe what I’m trying to say

author: conall
message:
Thanks for all you’ve said babes, I really appreciate it. I do think you’re right in the sense that I feel like I’m being dragged about this way and that. Over the years I’ve learned how my brain works and realised that habits are really the only thing that keeps me from spinning out and becoming a wreck. I am normally pretty good at just sticking with stuff but these last few weeks have just been quite all over the place.

I think it’s a combo of feeling like I don’t have much agency in my life (which obviously isn’t true in the fullest sense), and just feeling like nothing I can do is enough. I’ve got these two stag do’s to sort out along with a whole heap of other crap and I’m just shutting down a bit. I guess looking after my sisters dog and then moving her in etc, all to be told that she doesn’t have time to go for a catch up meal until April kinda stung too. Makes me feel like I’m just “useful” for people to have around. I’ve barely seen Dan since I moved her in her flat, because she’s off with her new life. It’s fine, but it just makes me feel like I’m just a dog’s body.

I know that’s not true if I think it through, it can’t be or else my life would be very different. It’s just been a few circumstances recently that have all stacked up on one another and my brain is mapping it all on to this grand narrative. I know it’s not true intellectually, it’s just hard to get there sometimes when there’s all these little bits of evidence

author: conall
message: And I know babes, don’t worry I don’t feel pressured by you or anything like that. I love hanging out with you, and I never want to give you the impression that you’re dragging me away from somewhere I’d rather be

author: Zoë “cringe” Turner
message:
I think you’re right my love, and this is all a lot to have going round in your head when you’re also trying to do your day to day stuff, and new things keep popping up. 

I do think there’s probably an element of thinking these things about yourself - that you can’t do enough, that you’re only useful to people etc. - maybe that’s always there, and then when these things happen in quick succession it kind of proves the narrative you’ve already built about yourself. Not to be all therapy about it, and they’re valid feelings to have given the circumstances, but sometimes these things start from the core of us don’t they. 

You’re an extremely giving person, and you’re hard on yourself. So I think sometimes those two things can collapse into each other and it’s easy for you to forget how much people love you, but people do love you an awful lot. Ok ????????????????????
